Class EnvironmentView

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible

    public class EnvironmentView
extends MyPanel
    This class implements the graphic view to show during the game.

    This class contains all the graphic elements needed to show the running game and the information resulting from it. This class extends from MyPanel which is a generic, standard view. The different elements that contains can be classified in three categories: configuration elements, information elements and field elements. The configuration elements category includes elements such as images sizes in percent, images names or reference coordinates. The information elements category includes elements such as JLabels to show information like team names, player names or the game score. The field elements category includes elements such as player's and ball's images and player's and ball's coordinates.

    Version:
    v0.1 04/18/2014
    Author:
    Eduard de Torres

        public void repaintPlayers(Coordinates[] teamA,
                  Coordinates[] teamB,
                  Ball ball)
        Repaints the player's and ball's images.

        Repaints the player's and ball's images from a set of given coordinates. If any of the given coordinates equals (-1,-1) the image won't be painted.

        Parameters:
        teamA - set of player's coordinates in a grid world representing the team A.
        teamB - set of player's coordinates in a grid world representing the team B.
        ball - coordinates in a grid world representing the ball's position.

      • whoHaveBall

        public java.lang.String whoHaveBall(int ball_x,
                           int ball_y)
        Returns an encoded string indicating who has the ball.

        Returns an encoded string indicating who has the ball. The encoding method has the format "T/N", where T can be {A, B} depending on which team has possession of the ball, and N represents the player's number in possession of the ball [-1..TEAM_SIZE] starting with -1 representing the goalkeeper. If noone has the ball, the method will return null.

        Parameters:
        ball_x - x-coordinate of the ball.
        ball_y - y-coordinate of the ball.
        Returns:
        null if noone has the ball. An encoded string if any player has the ball.

        public boolean checkValidPosition(boolean team_a,
                         int number,
                         Coordinates[] teamA,
                         Coordinates[] teamB)
        Returns whether a given players runs into any other player in the field.

        Returns whether the chosen player of one team runs into one of their teammates or against any of its rivals.

        Parameters:
        team_a - true if the player plays for team A.
        number - number of the player in his team.

        teamB - coordinates of all the players from team B.
        Returns:
        false if the player runs into any other player.
